Tony Hunt is demanding an apology from police after his daughter's cat Harry was hit by a patrol car near his home in Derby . 
  A neighbour reported the cat had been 'disposed of' by police officers who knocked on his door and asked for a black bin bag . 
  Mr Hunt is outraged as the ginger cat was micro-chipped and could have been contacted by police . 
  He is demanding a face-to-face apology from the two officers . 
 